## Welcome, welcome .... to the realm of Linux!

### Linux commands for forcing Git via Terminal

make a directory on your local computer
`mkdir ~/git_test`

find your current directory 
cd ~/git_test

#### 1. make the folder you created into a git repository 
`git init`

#### 2. create a file 
`touch README.md`

#### 3. ‘select’ the file you want to commit and push to git online 
`git add README.md`

To check what files have been selected
`git status`

#### 4. commit the selected files and add a note 
`git commit -m "Your commit message here"`

Create the repository online with the EXACT same name, as it now only exist on your local 

#### 5. add https to connect online repository to your

`git remote add origin <HTTPS_LINK>`

#### 6. push files 
`git push -u origin main`

### Updating your local git repository 
`git pull origin main`
